                    <p>To keep all the data safe and secure we use Secured Socket Layer (SSL). Data encryption, message integrity, and server authentication are the part of SSL system. A small lock at the bottom right or left corner of your browser window is present when you visit our website, this means the data of the user is safe and saved in encrypted form.</p>

                    <p>InfoPark shall not release any confidential information of a Subscriber unless an authenticated request from the Subscriber is received providing a specific reason for such request. However, if the release of information is required as per law, by the government, in that case, InfoPark shall reveal the information required. Our privacy policy is structured as per the Law of India.</p>

